summary: Completed comprehensive end-to-end testing of the Super App with all 4 service verticals (Food, Rides, Hotels, Provider Registration). All backend APIs and frontend pages are working perfectly. The dynamic service management system correctly shows 5 enabled services and 2 disabled services based on Command Center configuration.
passed_tests: GET /api/food/cuisines - returns 10 cuisine types with Arabic names and icons
GET /api/food/restaurants - API working (0 restaurants, empty state handled correctly)
GET /api/food/restaurants with filters - cuisine and featured filters working
GET /api/rides/types - returns 4 ride types (economy, comfort, premium, xl) with pricing
POST /api/rides/estimate - fare calculation working for all ride types (10-25 SAR range)
GET /api/hotels/cities - returns 8 cities with hotel counts
GET /api/hotels/search - API working with filters (0 hotels, empty state handled)
GET /api/join/available-services - returns 5 enabled and 2 disabled services dynamically
Error handling - 404 responses for invalid endpoints working correctly
/food page - loads correctly, shows cuisines grid, empty restaurants state, registration CTAs
/rides page - loads correctly, shows ride types, booking form, fare estimation UI
/hotels page - loads correctly, search form functional, city selection, date inputs working
/join page - shows 5 available services and 2 coming soon services correctly
/command/services - authentication working, services dashboard showing correct enabled/disabled status
Dynamic service filtering - Join page correctly reflects Command Center service settings
Arabic RTL interface - all text and layouts properly right-to-left oriented
Empty state handling - all service pages show appropriate messages when no data available
Navigation and CTAs - all registration links and service navigation working correctly
